OL,3,CWhy do the clocks go forward and what
OL,4,Cimpact does it have on your health?
OL,6,FMany dairy farmers actually complain
OL,7,Fthat it disrupts their schedule,
OL,8,Funsettling cows, which struggle to
OL,9,Fcope with the change.
OL,11,FIn Britain, daylight saving time was
OL,12,Ffirst proposed by builder William
OL,13,FWillett in 1907, in a pamphlet called
OL,14,FThe Waste Of Daylight, which outlined
OL,15,Fhis frustration with not getting the
OL,16,Fmost out of summer days.
OL,18,FWillett initially proposed that clocks
OL,19,Fjump forward by 80 minutes in four
OL,20,Fsteps in April and reversed the same
OL,21,Fway in September.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
