OL,3,CWhy do the clocks go forward and what
OL,4,Cimpact does it have on your health?
OL,6,FDr John O'Neill, a molecular biologist
OL,7,Fand expert in cellular rhythms from
OL,8,Fthe Cambridge-based Medical Research
OL,9,FCouncil Laboratory of Molecular
OL,10,FBiology, said there are "small but
OL,11,Fsignificant" risks due to the time
OL,12,Fchange.
OL,14,F"It does not really serve much of a
OL,15,Fbenefit to anybody these days, whilst
OL,16,Fexposing us to a small but significant
OL,17,Fseries of risks," he said.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
