PN,31907
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774696008
OL,3,CWhy do the clocks go forward and what
OL,4,Cimpact does it have on your health?
OL,6,F"It is like everybody in the country
OL,7,Fgets an hour's jet lag, all at the
OL,8,Fsame time. You see an increase in
OL,9,Fincidence of heart attacks and
OL,10,Fstrokes, and you do get an increase in
OL,11,Fthe number of road traffic accidents
OL,12,Ffor a few days after clocks change."
OL,14,FDr O'Neill said incidences of heart
OL,15,Fattacks and stroke increase because
OL,16,Four bodies anticipate daily activity
OL,17,Fat certain times, and when the clocks
OL,18,Fchange, our physiology is not primed
OL,19,Fand ready.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
