PN,31908
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F319A1774696008
OL,3,CWhy do the clocks go forward and what
OL,4,Cimpact does it have on your health?
OL,6,FHe said: "If you place all of those
OL,7,Fburdens and demands on, for example,
OL,8,Fthe cardiovascular system, an hour
OL,9,Fearlier, then it is just not quite as
OL,10,Fwell prepared to satisfy the demand,
OL,11,Fso in people that are a bit older or a
OL,12,Fbit less healthy, it increases their
OL,13,Frisk of an adverse event, a heart
OL,14,Fattack or a stroke."
OL,16,FShould daylight savings time be
OL,17,Fabolished?
OL,19,FPolling in recent years suggests that
OL,20,FBritons would prefer to stay on BST if
OL,21,Fthe time changes were scrapped.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
